5 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
6 MONTANA REQUESTING AN INTERIM STUDY OF MONTANA'S PROPERTY TAX SYSTEM; AND
7 REQUIRING THAT THE FINAL RESULTS OF THE STUDY BE REPORTED TO THE 70TH LEGISLATURE.
8
9 WHEREAS, property taxes are an important funding source for the state, cities, counties, school
10 districts, and special districts; and
11 WHEREAS, Montana’s 18 classes of property could be reduced to a few classes for simplification; and
12 WHEREAS, the state tax rates, valuation methods, exemptions, settlement procedures, and assistance
13 programs vary widely among classes, resulting in an overly complicated property tax system.
14
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
16 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
17 That the Legislative Council be requested to designate an appropriate interim committee or statutory
18 committee, pursuant to section 5-5-217, MCA, to study Montana's property tax system.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the study include:
20 (1) an overview of the property tax classes and the tax rates and valuation methods used for each
21 class;
22 (2) a review of property tax exemptions, including the types of exemptions and the loss of taxable
23 value and taxes resulting from the exemptions;
24 (3) a review of settlements between taxpayers and the Department of Revenue; and
25 (4) consideration of options for consolidating tax classes, equalizing appraisals, and balancing tax
26 liabilities between classes.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that all aspects of the study, including presentation and review
28 requirements, be concluded prior to September 15, 2026.
